New Reading Series No Drop in the Bucket<br/><br/>I &lt;a href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.christian-louboutin-shoes.cc%26quot%3B%26gt%3Bchristian"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.christian-louboutin-shoes.cc&quot;&gt;christian</a> louboutin shoes&lt;/a&gt;am thrilled to report that last week’s inaugural reading of the Mad Poets Society’s new Center City Series at the Last Drop was a rousing success! 
<br /><br />Poets&lt;a href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.christian-louboutin-shoes.cc%2Fchristian_louboutin_pumps.html%26quot%3B%26gt%3Bchristian"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.christian-louboutin-shoes.cc/christian_louboutin_pumps.html&quot;&gt;christian</a> louboutin pumps&lt;/a&gt;  and friends packed into the cozy basement venue and even converted a few unsuspecting coffee sippers into audience members. But how could they not stay: JAZ’s poems and songs triumphed over the upstairs sound system — particularly her goose-bump inducing rendition of Sarah McLachlan’s “Possession.” And although, I must admit I would happily listen to Ashraf Osman, in his sultry Lebanese accent, read passages from a VCR manual, it was the unexpected metaphors peppered throughout his poems that stunned me over and over again. You should read them; they will rip the hair off your head!
<br /><br />Along&lt;a href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jimmy-choo-shoes.com%26quot%3B%26gt%3Bjimmy"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.jimmy-choo-shoes.com&quot;&gt;jimmy</a> choo sale&lt;/a&gt; with these excellent featured readers, we were joined by 5 fine area poets in the open mic. And, of course, the coffee was tasty, the chairs were comfy, and the host (*winkwink*) was charming and ebullient. As far as I can tell, this series has what it takes to be one of the most eclectic outlets for Philly poets. 
